author: Times-News
title: Towson tops Elon in four sets in volleyball
text: Posted Oct. 5, 2015 at 12:38 AM Updated at 12:40 AM Posted Oct. 5, 2015 at 12:38 AM Updated at 12:40 AM ELON â€” Jocelyn Kuilan had a match-high 17 kills to lead Towson as the visiting Tigers defeated Elon 25-14, 25-20, 20-25, 25-18 in Colonial Athletic Association volleyball Sunday afternoon at Alumni Gym. The Phoenix (3-14 overall, 0-4 CAA) was led by Sydney Busa and Ally Karle with a team-high 12 kills apiece. Sydel Curry had a match-high 34 assists and Catherine Head paced Elon with four blocks. Towson improved to 16-2, 3-1. By Times-News
